1 L.D. 140
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 76, L.D. 140, “An Act to Incrementally
10 Increase the Homestead Property Tax Exemption”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1-B by striking out all of paragraph C (page
12 1, lines 11 to 13 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 'C. For property tax years beginning on or after April 1, 2020, $15,000 of the just value
14 of the homestead; and'
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1-B in paragraph D in the first line (page 1,
16 line 14 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "$10,000" and inserting the following:
17 '$5,000'
18 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1-B in paragraph D in the last line (page 1,
19 line 16 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "$85,000" and inserting the following:
20 '$50,000'
21 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1-B in the first blocked paragraph in the last
22 line (page 1, line 22 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "2032" and inserting the
23 following: '2031'
24 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
25 'Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
26 allocations are made.
27 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
28 Revenue Services, Bureau of 0002
29 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for computer programming costs.
30 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
31 All Other $47,640 $0
32 __________ __________
33 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $47,640 $0
3340 Revenue Services, Bureau of 0002
